The Chronicle Nqobile Tshili, Chronicle Reporter THIEVES last night broke into Bulawayo Mayor councillor Solomon Mguni’s car and stole cash among other valuables at his home in Nkulumane suburb. <img class="alignnone wp-image-530225 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/02/Byo-mayor-looking-into-his-car.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/02/Byo-mayor-looking-into-his-car.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/02/Byo-mayor-looking-into-his-car-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Cllr Mguni discovered the crime on Thursday morning. He said he had forgotten his wallet in the vehicle and the thieves also got away with his car battery. <img class="alignnone wp-image-530228 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/02/Bulawayo-mayor-looking-into-his-car-2.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/02/Bulawayo-mayor-looking-into-his-car-2.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/02/Bulawayo-mayor-looking-into-his-car-2-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Nkulumane suburb is one of the six western suburbs that police identified as hotspots for burglary cases which in some instances lead to women being raped. More details to follow…